                <h1>Roe v. Wade: A Landmark Case in Abortion Rights</h1>
                <p>Roe v. Wade was a landmark Supreme Court case in 1973 that legalized abortion nationwide. The case involved a woman, "Jane Roe," who challenged Texas laws prohibiting abortion. The court ruled that the right to privacy encompassed a woman's decision to terminate her pregnancy, igniting a decades-long debate over reproductive rights.</p>
